      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "CFD solver must have documented V&V test suite and configuration-controlled release for MRL 5 device submissions.",
      "rationale": "The CFD solver (ANSYS Fluent 2022R2) has a documented QA plan and version control; however, the hemolysis user-defined function (UDF) implementing the power-law damage model lacks a formal unit-test suite. Achieved level 3 — version control present but UDF verification incomplete relative to required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Method of manufactured solutions or equivalent analytical benchmark must confirm solver implementation correctness for the turbulence and scalar transport equations used.",
      "rationale": "Verification was limited to a lid-driven cavity benchmark for the flow solver. No manufactured-solution verification was performed for the scalar hemolysis transport equation. Achieved level 2 falls short of required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Richardson extrapolation or GCI analysis on at least three mesh levels; discretization error must be reported as a percentage of QoI.",
      "rationale": "GCI analysis was conducted on three mesh levels (4.2 M, 11.6 M, 28.4 M cells). GCI for pressure head is 1.8%; GCI for hemolysis index is 6.3%, exceeding the 5% target. Achieved level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental boundary conditions (inlet flow rate, rotational speed, fluid temperature, hematocrit) must be documented with measurement uncertainty for all validation operating points.",
      "rationale": "Inlet flow rate and rotational speed are documented for all five operating points. Fluid temperature and hematocrit were reported as nominal values only; measurement uncertainty on these quantities is not available in the published dataset. Achieved level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative agreement metric (e.g., normalised RMS error) with combined simulation and experimental uncertainty bounds reported for each QoI at each operating point.",
      "rationale": "Normalised RMS error across five operating points is 18.4% for hemolysis index. Simulation uncertainty from Monte Carlo UQ is reported; experimental uncertainty is partially characterised. Combined uncertainty bands overlap at 3 of 5 operating points. Achieved level 3 — partial uncertainty characterisation prevents level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The validation QoI (hemolysis index) must directly correspond to the clinical acceptance criterion (absolute hemolysis below threshold).",
      "rationale": "The normalised index of hemolysis (NIH) used in validation directly maps to the clinical threshold specified in the COU. QoI relevance is well-established in the literature. Achieved level 3 meets required level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments must use the same pump geometry, blood analogue fluid, and operating envelope as the COU. Any differences must be assessed for their impact on predictive accuracy.",
      "rationale": "Validation used the FDA generic pump geometry and a glycerol-water blood analogue. The COU device is a proprietary centrifugal pump with different impeller geometry. No formal similarity analysis quantifying the geometric and fluid-property differences was performed. Achieved level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
