    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Despite multiple credibility factor gaps, the assessment team accepted the package on the basis that the Monte Carlo UQ results demonstrate hemolysis predictions remain below the clinical threshold across the full sampled input space, and that the normalised RMS error of 18.4% is within the pre-specified acceptable range for a Low assurance level submission. Remaining gaps in equivalency, test samples, and use error are acknowledged as epistemic limitations to be addressed in a follow-on MRL 5 submission.",
